HEADWORD: Brankursine
<hw>Brank"ur*sine</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>branc-ursine</ets>, <ets>branch-ursine</ets>, fr. LL.
<ets>branca</ets> claw + L. <ets>ursinus</ets> belonging to a bear (fr.
<ets>ursus</ets> bear), <it>i. e.</it>, bear's claw, because its leaves
resemble the claws of a bear. Cf. <er>Branch</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Bear's-breech, or Acanthus.</def>⟦br⟧
